227
00:18:38,860 --> 00:18:43,480
But God also set up that garden and wanted Adam to tend to it,

228
00:18:43,520 --> 00:18:47,160
that it might not become a wilderness, that it might be a beautiful garden.

229
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:53,360
He designed it so that Adam would work with God in the preservation of the garden.

230
00:18:54,510 --> 00:18:57,010
God wants our dependence on Him for everything.

231
00:18:58,070 --> 00:19:01,690
But in a sense, He's also set up the world to depend on us.

232
00:19:01,690 --> 00:19:08,150
He needs us to be involved in things in the world where things get out of control.

233
00:19:14,650 --> 00:19:17,130
There's a story of the man who came upon a stone quarry.

234
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:24,680
A number of men were working, and one said, well, what am I doing?

235
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:26,440
He said, well, I'm digging stone.

236
00:19:27,860 --> 00:19:28,960
That's one way to look at it.

237
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:32,240
The other one, when turned to, said, what are you doing here?

238
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:34,060
He says, well, I'm earning $100 a week.

239
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:37,080
One way to look at your work.

240
00:19:37,080 --> 00:19:42,700
The third man stuck his chest out, and he said, I'm building a cathedral.

241
00:19:44,390 --> 00:19:45,730
I'm building a cathedral.

242
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:49,520
He's serving the Lord in his work.

243
00:19:50,520 --> 00:19:53,100
What he's doing has impact in the kingdom,

244
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:57,660
building a place for people to gather and express their love to God.

245
00:19:58,420 --> 00:20:02,240
God has us co-labor with him to accomplish his purposes,

246
00:20:02,620 --> 00:20:06,520
and when that happens, friends, work can become, and listen to this,

247
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:09,920
work can become an expression of worship.

248
00:20:11,730 --> 00:20:13,990
Work can become an expression of worship.

249
00:20:14,550 --> 00:20:17,490
It's not that we worship our jobs,

250
00:20:18,260 --> 00:20:20,240
but our jobs can be an expression

251
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:23,560
of us giving worship to God.

252
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:28,460
The Bible says in Colossians 3.23,

253
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:31,540
sorry, rather 1 Corinthians 10.31, the first one,

254
00:20:31,540 --> 00:20:35,980
so whether you eat or drink or whatever you do,

255
00:20:37,170 --> 00:20:39,950
Do it all for the glory of God.

256
00:20:41,690 --> 00:20:44,110
Can you be a policeman for the glory of God?

257
00:20:44,370 --> 00:20:45,210
You bet.

258
00:20:46,730 --> 00:20:48,730
You are bringing peace to a community.

259
00:20:49,940 --> 00:20:51,600
You bless others in your work.

260
00:20:53,330 --> 00:20:56,770
And you can do it with excellence and with high morals and high integrity,

261
00:20:56,970 --> 00:20:58,750
and it's an act of worship unto God.

262
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:02,520
Can you be an artist for the Lord?

263
00:21:02,760 --> 00:21:03,240
Absolutely.

264
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:06,180
Be a teacher unto God?

265
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:07,480
Absolutely.

266
00:21:09,140 --> 00:21:12,980
Think of all the occupations and all the calling and all the jobs in this room,

267
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:18,920
and each one can be done as an expression of worship when done under the service of the Lord.

268
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:21,120
Colossians 3.23 says,

269
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:23,840
Work hard and cheerfully at whatever you do,

270
00:21:24,690 --> 00:21:28,890
as though you were working for the Lord rather than for people.

271
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:32,480
That'll blow your boss's mind.

272
00:21:33,790 --> 00:21:36,490
When you go in and you do everything they say,

273
00:21:36,750 --> 00:21:39,190
but really you're not working just to please them.

274
00:21:39,850 --> 00:21:41,330
You're working to please the Lord.

275
00:21:42,110 --> 00:21:44,230
This job is unto the Lord.

276
00:21:46,580 --> 00:21:50,700
Transcribing code in the World War II is a way to say,

277
00:21:50,840 --> 00:21:54,580
Lord, I give you my skills, and this space is sacred space

278
00:21:54,580 --> 00:21:56,740
because I'm with you and you're with me,

279
00:21:56,760 --> 00:21:58,860
and we're going to do this unto the Lord.

280
00:22:01,430 --> 00:22:02,690
Work can be a sacred space.

281
00:22:02,690 --> 00:22:04,910
Have you ever thought about your work as a place

282
00:22:04,910 --> 00:22:07,790
where you bring God into your world,

283
00:22:09,110 --> 00:22:11,690
where you can honor him with your excellent craftsmanship,

284
00:22:11,690 --> 00:22:15,390
your excellent attitude, with your excellent skills that God has given you,

285
00:22:15,530 --> 00:22:19,270
and bless the community by the product, whatever it is that you put out,

286
00:22:19,850 --> 00:22:24,610
whether it's a widget or transforming people or anything that you do,

287
00:22:25,580 --> 00:22:26,480
it's an act of worship.

288
00:22:29,460 --> 00:22:31,440
According to the Puritans, Tim Downs writes,

289
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:35,020
all professions are spiritual to the Christian,

290
00:22:35,120 --> 00:22:37,040
not because of the nature of the work,

291
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:40,860
but because of the presence of God in you.

292
00:22:42,320 --> 00:22:46,720
And he writes, when a Christian, the temple of the Holy Spirit, walks into an office at

293
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:50,420
IBM, IBM becomes a sacred space.

294
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:55,140
The hospital that you work in becomes a sacred space.

295
00:22:55,830 --> 00:22:59,130
The engineering firm becomes a sacred space.

296
00:22:59,590 --> 00:23:08,200
The theater, the office, wherever you are, whether you're retired or whether you're actively

297
00:23:08,200 --> 00:23:12,940
working, wherever you are becomes sacred space because God is in you and you bring God into

298
00:23:12,940 --> 00:23:13,640
those spaces.

299
00:23:15,310 --> 00:23:18,760
What a calling, what a privilege to co-create with God

300
00:23:18,760 --> 00:23:21,600
and let Him use you to bless the community

301
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:25,120
and to live out in your work as an act of worship.

302
00:23:27,740 --> 00:23:29,380
Work can be a service for God.

303
00:23:30,860 --> 00:23:34,780
It also is a blessing to God as you bring Jesus into your workplace

304
00:23:34,780 --> 00:23:39,260
because there, through your work, through your attitude, through your excellence,

305
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:43,340
through how you relate to others, people will notice that you are different

306
00:23:43,340 --> 00:23:46,930
because you're not working just to impress the boss.

307
00:23:46,930 --> 00:23:55,260
you're working to bless the Lord. And friends, that will get noticed. It really will. Because

308
00:23:55,260 --> 00:24:01,900
you're the worker that's there on time with ethics. You're the one who actually speaks well

309
00:24:01,900 --> 00:24:08,760
of others. You hold your tongue when you want to lash out. You are different in your work. That's

310
00:24:08,760 --> 00:24:14,240
how our work is transformed by Jesus. We are different in how we approach it, how we do it,

311
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:16,280
and how we bring Him to it.

312
00:24:18,780 --> 00:24:20,340
And friends, when you work in the world,

313
00:24:20,440 --> 00:24:23,480
you are living out the hands and feet of Jesus.

314
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:26,660
Way before your friend comes to visit here,

315
00:24:27,620 --> 00:24:30,500
they're seeing Jesus in you out there.

316
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:33,820
And what a high calling and privilege that is,

317
00:24:33,860 --> 00:24:37,420
is to express Jesus in your occupations in the world today.

318
00:24:39,060 --> 00:24:40,500
And so when you leave this sanctuary,

319
00:24:41,020 --> 00:24:45,480
we send you with Jesus and the Holy Spirit out into the world

320
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:48,980
to change it and to live out the values of the kingdom

321
00:24:48,980 --> 00:24:51,500
in whatever workplace you have.

322
00:24:53,030 --> 00:24:54,730
Whether you're raising children or grandchildren

323
00:24:54,730 --> 00:24:56,910
or working in a big office building

324
00:24:56,910 --> 00:24:59,430
or outside or inside, it doesn't matter.

325
00:24:59,550 --> 00:25:00,310
It's all sacred.

326
00:25:00,690 --> 00:25:02,150
It's all work unto the Lord.

327
00:25:03,720 --> 00:25:04,000
Wow.

328
00:25:06,740 --> 00:25:09,280
So, do we live, thank God it's Friday?

329
00:25:09,940 --> 00:25:12,410
Or thank God it's Monday?

330
00:25:13,440 --> 00:25:16,280
I can live out these experiences unto God

331
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:18,220
as I go to work.

332
00:25:18,220 --> 00:25:22,500
I hope you enjoy tomorrow as a day off

333
00:25:22,500 --> 00:25:24,840
I hope for many of you that will be a day off

334
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:26,720
and I hope Tuesday morning comes around

335
00:25:26,720 --> 00:25:29,480
and you say Lord I am yours

336
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:30,860
this is your day

337
00:25:30,860 --> 00:25:32,420
may I live for you

338
00:25:32,420 --> 00:25:36,020
and may my work be transformed in some way

339
00:25:36,020 --> 00:25:38,110
what a privilege and an honor

340
00:25:38,110 --> 00:25:42,450
and may your co-workers see Jesus in you

341
00:25:42,450 --> 00:25:45,790
so with that there's a song that David's going to sing

342
00:25:45,790 --> 00:25:48,070
expresses that very value

343
00:25:48,070 --> 00:25:50,840
that as you get out there into the world,

344
00:25:52,030 --> 00:25:54,790
your relationship with Christ will transform you

345
00:25:54,790 --> 00:25:59,520
and others will see Jesus for the first time in you.

346
00:26:00,660 --> 00:26:01,880
Dave, would you share with us?

